title.49: Spider-Man: Spirits of the Earth Graphic Novel (1990)

description.8: Doctor Strange is battered, exhausted from his brutal gauntlet of new and surprising foes. But he's not out of the fire yet, as ARKON makes his move!
description.9: It's the team-up you demanded — the Punisher and Spider-Man! And to make things even wilder, Spidey's got the Captain Universe powers!
description.13: Daredevil's battle with Ultron comes to a head - and someone pays a terrible price.
description.14: Meggan and Rachel's powers are clashing, which spells disaster for Excalibur! Can the team save Meggan, stop a train from derailing, AND defeat Brian's alternate evil sister all at the same time!?
description.15: Featuring Excalibur's Phoenix and Power Pack! Reed and Sue suspect a trap when the Four Freedoms Plaza takes on the appearance of the old Baxter Building. The past, present and future loop out of sync in this time-tossed tale!
description.16: Powerhouse vs. Powerhouse! The Hulk goes head-to-head with the Fantastic Four's THING!
description.17: Loki sent out his gun in Wrecker -- now it's Kingpin's turn! Chemistro arrives to spill Iron Man's blood. An unlikely hero rises.
description.19: Continued from Fantastic Four Annual #23! Franklin Richards is all grown up, and with him comes trouble.
description.21: Thor and Herc visit Doctor Strange to discover the source of the mysterious ills that plague them...and it's a doozy! Plus, a backup story featuring Beta Ray Bill!
description.22: ACTS OF VENGEANCE Spider-Man takes on Goliath. But that's just the appetizer. What Doom has planned for the main course is something altogether more sinister...
description.23: X-Factor must unite a divided alien planet against the Celestials who have come to judge them. While on Earth, the wheels of the Acts of Vengeance have started to turn...
description.24: Franklin has to make a difficult choice between creating his ideal world and taking down the evil Ahab!
description.25: Alpha Flight attempts to round up the defecting villains, when Canadian law enforcement demands that the group disband!
description.26: The Fantastic Four is having a hard enough time convincing Congress to stop a law controlling superhumans, but things really get out of hand when a secret device hypnotizes everyone - and makes them attack the team!
description.27: In the service of the Hand and the Mandarin, the brain-washed Psylocke establishes herself as Lady Mandarin, reestablishing the Mandarin's control over the Hong Kong underworld.
description.28: Does Wolverine stand a chance fighting Tiger Shark in his own waters? Meanwhile, Sister Salvation tests out her mutant strength on the rapidly weakening Roughouse.
description.31: Acts of Vengeance! The Mole Man takes his shot at the Avengers West Coast as the villains plan to enact vengeance kicks into high gear!
description.32: Acts of Vengeance continues as Quasar contends with a litany of looters including Venom, Klaw, and the Living Laser!
description.33: THE FATE OF THE PHOENIX! It's the Shi'ar versus the X-Men in an epic duel on the blue area of the Moon! Winner decides the fate of the Dark Phoenix! Can Cyclops save his love? Or is she doomed to die at the hand of the Shi'ar? Witness the iconic climax to one of the greatest X-Men stories ever told, beautifully remastered!
description.35: While on a stakeout, Frank Castle learns that a volatile weapon will be up for grabs on the Black Market. Punisher teams with an American journalist to blow the lid on this story, but they’re inadvertently pulled into a criminal underbelly of thieves, cutthroats and stone cold killers.
description.36: The New Mutants are stuck in a nightmarish world of television. Can the team escape this doom tube reality?
description.44: These red eyed cannibals have their sights set on Conan!
description.45: ACTS OF VENGEANCE This battle between the Hulk and Spider-Man begs the question: "Now who's the strongest one there is?!" Plus: The mutant menace of Sebastian Shaw!
description.46: The time is now! The final showdown vs. Terminus to save the planet Earth!
description.47: Super-villain team up! After Mandarin and Wizard grow tired of planning an attack on the Avengers, they decide to spring into ill-fated action. The Avengers vs. Mandarin, Wizard, Dr. Doom, Loki, and Kingpin!
description.48: The Red Skull orders Crossbones to help the super-villains who've escaped from the Vault. And to stop Captain America from intercepting him, the Red Skull sends Iron Man's enemy, the Controller!
description.49: Peter and Mary Jane’s romantic getaway in Scotland turns into a haunted second honeymoon!
description.50: ACTS OF VENGEANCE Spider-Man must face the Master of Magnetism himself: Magneto! Plus, will Spider-Man's new powers prove to be a blessing or a curse?
description.53: The tit for tat battle rages on between Hulk and the Abomination! And the Abomination will walk away from this one scarred- physically and mentally.
description.57: Frank Castle vs. Bushwacker – and all at the will of the indomitable Kingpin!
description.62: ACTS OF VENGEANCE Doctor Doom sends Titania after the now Cosmic-powered Spider-Man!
description.63: The FF are off to Washington DC! The team is called to a hearing in Congress about a potential law for superhuman registration, but will the event be able to finish without super-villains crashing the party?
description.64: The Avengers' lives continue to spin out of control after Freedom Force attacks Avengers Park. What provoked Freedom Force? And which heroes will fall in battle?
description.65: The Red Skull employs the Controller to hypnotize Namor into attacking Captain America. You won't believe how this battle ends!
description.69: ACTS OF VENGEANCE continues to plague Doctor Strange! The Sorcerer Supreme has defeated warlocks, demons and evil spirits, but can he take on ASGARDIANS? The Executioner and Enchantress set their sights on Stephen Strange!
description.70: Brain-washed X-Man Psylocke has been hired out as an assassin for The Mandarin. What follows is a nightmarish Mojoverse transformation for Psylocke. Witness the strange origin of Betsey Braddock's transformation into Japanese ninja.
description.74: ACTS OF VENGEANCE crashes headlong into the life of Doctor Strange! As villains switch nemeses to catch the heroes off guard, Strange finds himself facing off with the sinister HOBGOBLIN!
description.75: An Acts Of Vengeance crossover! The Punisher takes on the Bushwacker— and both discover some disturbing things about the other!
description.77: ACTS OF VENGEANCE comes for The Man Without Fear! Daredevil has fought off some of the deadliest threats in the Marvel Universe -- but can even he survive the might of ULTRON...and DOCTOR DOOM?
description.78: Freedom Force has arrived on Muir Island and a new line-up of X-Men must subdue the incoming villains. Destiny plays a mind-game with Legion...with deadly consequence. As if Mystique and her Freedom Force weren't enough, Donald Pierce arrives with The Reavers...and the mutant-terrorists are armed to the teeth with dangerous tech.
description.79: Villains are defecting to Canada to bypass the Super Human Registration Act, with a helping hand from the Sorcerer.
description.81: Kurt Wagner, Space Pirate, embarks on his own intergalactic adventure!
description.82: To save the world from unknown assassins, a new Champion must rise! And Excalibur plans to find out who deserves that role by holding a tournament! But will it be in time?
description.83: The Gray Gargoyle has just turned the Hulk into unmoving stone! Too bad no one told the Hulk!
description.84: Iron Man and Doom are brought to the future to face their legacies. Guest starring: Doctor Doom and Merlin!
description.85: Loki recruits the Wrecker to fell Iron Man at Stark Prosthetics!
description.89: The Judgment War continues! The battle rages on throughout the alien planet while Celestials descend upon the world! But X-Factor must first escape their variou inprisonments before they can stop the war or avoid the Celestials!
description.90: Iceman and Archangel must fight each other in the arena! Meanwhile, Loki has an offer for Apocalypse regarding the Acts of Vengeance!
description.91: Break-in at the Baxter Building! A motley crew of villains begins storming the headquarters of the Fantastic Four, but are they trying to take out the team? Or is there another hidden goal behind these intrusions?
description.92: There's a new X-team line-up! Featuring Banshee, Moira MacTaggert, Legion, Amanda Sefton and Polaris. With unique skill-sets and abilities, this new roster will be handling the many threats that endanger mutantkind, and taking some of the load off the regular X-team.
description.96: What is the shocking truth behind the Scarlet Witch's children? Enter: Master Pandemonium!
description.97: Acts of Vengeance!  The U-Foes arrive to take on the Avengers West Coast!
description.98: What if Wolverine had become an Agent of S.H.I.E.L.D.? Instead of joining the All-New, All-Different Uncanny X-Men, Wolverine accepts an offer by Nick Fury to become a super spy taking on the likes of Hydra. And when threats come for mutantkind, how can Wolverine use his position in S.H.I.E.L.D. to protect his fellow mutants?
description.99: What if Iron Man lost the Armor Wars? When Tony Stark's designs for the Iron Man armor hit the open market, Tony takes it on himself to put an end to the villainous and mercenary uses of his armor design. But if he can't put the toothpaste back into the tube, what deadly and personal tragedies will befall Tony?

1.text: SPIDEY’S TOTALLY TINY ADVENTURE PART 1 This is definitely big trouble for little Spidey. Featuring Ant-Man!

6.text: ACTS OF VENGEANCE After Spidey's taken down Shocker, Rhino, and Hydro Man, who can possibly stand up to all-new all-powerful Cosmic hero?! Doctor Doom knows who!

7.text: What if the original X-Men died on their first mission? Professor Xavier mourns the loss of his X-Men and New X-Men after the teams perish on the island of Krakoa. Mutancy has a new face when Scarlet Witch and Quicksilver step in as reserve members of the X-Men!

8.text: Doctor Strange is battered, exhausted from his brutal gauntlet of new and surprising foes. But he's not out of the fire yet, as ARKON makes his move!

9.text: It's the team-up you demanded — the Punisher and Spider-Man! And to make things even wilder, Spidey's got the Captain Universe powers!

10.text: THE CHAOS SERPENT PART 1 You'd think that with the menace of the Death's Head Guard finally resolved, Nick could go back to the life he wants to lead. Well, Leviathan and the Coven are about to change Nick's plans forever!

11.text: Captain America unleashes a virus which disrupts nature itself! Wild animals, including humans, are afflicted with uncontrollable rage because of the termini strand. Iron Man goes rogue! Can Cap put the kibosh on what he accidentally started?

20.text: Her teammates must prevent a possessed-by-Hela Mirage from doing the unspeakable -- unleashing Ragnarok on Asgard!

25.text: Alpha Flight attempts to round up the defecting villains, when Canadian law enforcement demands that the group disband!

28.text: Tierra Verde's in the midst of civil war - but for Tiger Shark, his fight with Wolverine is strictly an Act of Vengeance! Plus: the revival of Roughouse and the secrets of Sister Salvation!

29.text: Silver Surfer may reconsider being a pacifist after going head-to-head with frequent Fantastic Four pest the Impossible Man!

32.text: Acts of Vengeance continues as Quasar contends with a litany of looters including Venom, Klaw, and the Living Laser!

34.text: Who is behind the costumed Pseudo-Man? She-Hulk must break the illusion before Lexington Loopner pays the price.

36.text: The New Mutants are stuck in a nightmarish world of television. Can the team escape this doom tube reality?

37.text: Someone is out to destroy the Savage Land! Wolverine pulls out all stops to prevent this second annihilation. But wait'll you see who he has to fight!

38.text: An Acts of Vengeance crossover! Killer Shrike is coming for Spector’s blood…and all of Moon Knight’s gadgets can’t save him! Will Frenchie be able to pull off a desperate rescue of MK?

39.text: Dr. Toulema was the man who gave the Morituri their powers. So why do the Morituri have to find and kill him?

40.text: Hawkeye and Mockingbird might sustain some hearing damage when they take on Angar the Screamer and Screaming Mimi!

41.text: Typhoid Mary poses as a teacher at a school for the blind in order to interfere with Power Pack and their happy home life!

42.text: Punisher must escape from Doom's castle in Latveria AND find a way to get the Kingpin off his back.

43.text: The future of the Shadowmasters (and even Punisher) is determined here! Three ninja masters vs. the entire Sunrise Society! Sure, the odds may seem stacked against our heroes, but the stakes have never been this high. Who survives this issue? Our lips are sealed!

49.text: Peter and Mary Jane’s romantic getaway in Scotland turns into a haunted second honeymoon!

52.text: Contains only Panther’s Quest Part 25: Dawn Reunion. PANTHER’S QUEST CONCLUSION: T’Challa must defeat Gore in single combat to find his mother and learn what has really kept her from Wakanda all these years.

54.text: Warlock and Boom-Boom get in way over their heads with Hrimhari, wolf demi-god!

55.text: With the New Warriors on the scene, Thor is given the opportunity to recollect his strength during his battle the Juggernaut. Will they be enough to halt the unstoppable?

56.text: ACTS OF VENGEANCE More powerful! More dangerous! More uncontrollable than ever before! Here comes the Cosmic Spidey! But will all that power make a difference against the magical might of the Brothers Grimm?!

57.text: Frank Castle vs. Bushwacker – and all at the will of the indomitable Kingpin!

58.text: It's Morituri versus Morituri in the most devastating manhunt the Earth of the future has seen! If you like stories loaded with high-tech action, this adventure's for you!

59.text: It seems unlikely that Moon Knight or Punisher will be “Called to Heaven” after this issue! After all, the two are going blow-for-blow against Ultimatum and its anarchic agents!

60.text: The PUNISHER brings the fight to Latveria when he's targeted by Doctor Doom!

61.text: Contains Panther’s Quest Part 24: Opponents and Hellcat in "Encounter in the Alley of Death". PANTHER’S QUEST PART 24: T’Challa fights an animal trap and a guard dog on his way to Pretorius' hideout.

66.text: Jennifer Walters takes on a high-profile prosecution, but it’s her Super Hero self that may land in hot water!

67.text: Nick Fury is up for assasination by the Death's Head, and time is against him. Will allies become trusted friends in this tale of ultimate suspense? The final chapter of Nick Fury vs. the Death's Head Commandos!

68.text: Wolverine just arrived in Tierra Verde, and he's already got a new ally, the freedom fighter called La Bandera, and a new opponent, longtime Avengers enemy Tiger Shark! Featuring the Kingpin, Magneto and more in an Acts of Vengeance crossover!

69.text: ACTS OF VENGEANCE continues to plague Doctor Strange! The Sorcerer Supreme has defeated warlocks, demons and evil spirits, but can he take on ASGARDIANS? The Executioner and Enchantress set their sights on Stephen Strange!

71.text: Things look like they can't get any worse after the destruction of Avengers Island. With morale low, the mischievous Loki releases Juggernaut from the confines of his prison. With Thor on the way, can a new group of teen heroes save the day?

72.text: ACTS OF VENGEANCE Now he's the strongest hero in the Marvel Universe! This is it! Spidey goes Cosmic!

73.text: This is it, folks! The peak of battle between Nick Fury and the Death's Head Commandos! Plus, the origin of Lump and the incredible return of S.H.I.E.L.D.!

74.text: ACTS OF VENGEANCE crashes headlong into the life of Doctor Strange! As villains switch nemeses to catch the heroes off guard, Strange finds himself facing off with the sinister HOBGOBLIN!

75.text: An Acts Of Vengeance crossover! The Punisher takes on the Bushwacker— and both discover some disturbing things about the other!

76.text: Contains only Panther’s Quest Part 23: Barriers. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 23: T’Challa arrives at the estate of Anton Pretorius, only to be attacked by Miyo Moshigo.

79.text: Villains are defecting to Canada to bypass the Super Human Registration Act, with a helping hand from the Sorcerer.

80.text: A family spat turns into a chase for survival when Daredevil faces off with the INHUMANS!

86.text: Contains only Panther’s Quest Part 22: Saying Good-bye. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 22: Riebeeck and Van der Merwe try to shoot down T’Challa’s glider before he can reach Pretorius.

87.text: Dani Moonstar -- the sole Valkyrie who can free herself from Hela’s possession! But what happens if she kills her fellow New Mutants first?

89.text: The JUDGMENT WAR continues! The battle rages on throughout the alien planet while Celestials descend upon the world! But X-Factor must first escape their various imprisonments before they can stop the war or avoid the Celestials!

93.text: The gruesome Geist wants Roughouse for a South American experiment, but he's got another buyer for Wolverine! Guest-starring Nuke!

94.text: It’s the dramatic, giant-sized conclusion to the Kree/Skrull War! And to make things even more chaotic, here comes the Living Tribunal!

95.text: The Surfer becomes the greatest threat to all life in the universe! How it happens makes this one of the greatest suspense stories of all time!
